description: Delicately seasoned fish fillets served on a bed of trail mix couscous, served with yoghurt, coriander and lemon wedges.
name: MoroccanStyle Fish With Trail Mix Couscous Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 500g frozen ocean selections fish fillets skinless Moroccan, thawed
1 lemon, cut into wedges, to serve

recipeInstructions.text: Heat a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook trail mix for 2 minutes, stirring, or until warmed through. Transfer to a bowl.
Heat half of the oil in same pan over mediumhigh heat. Cook fish according to packet instructions. Transfer to a plate. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, place couscous in a large heatproof bowl. Pour over 1 cup boiling water and stir to combine. Stand for 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork to separate grains. Stir in trail mix. Combine yoghurt and chopped coriander in a small bowl. Season.

Heat remaining oil in same cleaned pan over mediumhigh heat. Cook zucchini and garlic for 2 minutes, stirring, or until just tender. Divide couscous among plates. Top with zucchini mixture and fish. Top with yoghurt and remaining coriander. Season with pepper. Serve with lemon wedges.
